# Core Rule: Portfolio Kill/Greenlight Criteria

**Goal**: Establish clear kill/greenlight criteria to avoid wasting resources on bad bets.

## Rule

Every product idea must pass kill/greenlight criteria before entering validation or engineering.

## Greenlight Criteria (All Must Be True)

### Portfolio Score
- ✅ Portfolio Score ≥ 20 (High Priority or Portfolio Priority)

### Signal Strength
- ✅ Signal Strength ≥ 4 (Strong or Very Strong signals)

### TAM-for-Niche
- ✅ TAM-for-Niche ≥ 4 (Large or Very Large TAM)

### Moat Potential
- ✅ Moat Potential ≥ 4 (High or Very High moat potential)

### Implementation Cost
- ✅ Implementation Cost ≤ 3 (Very Low, Low, or Moderate cost)

### Long-Term Retention Risk
- ✅ Long-Term Retention Risk ≤ 3 (Very Low, Low, or Moderate risk)

### Monetization Depth
- ✅ Monetization Depth ≥ 4 (Deep or Very Deep monetization)

### Expected Value
- ✅ Expected Value ≥ $10k

### Risk Score
- ✅ Risk Score ≤ 15 (Low Risk or Very Low Risk)

### Capacity
- ✅ Engineering capacity available

## Kill Criteria (Kill if Any Are True)

### Portfolio Score
- ❌ Portfolio Score < 10

### Signal Strength
- ❌ Signal Strength = 1 (No signals)

### TAM-for-Niche
- ❌ TAM-for-Niche = 1 (Very small TAM)

### Moat Potential
- ❌ Moat Potential = 1 (Very low moat potential)

### Implementation Cost
- ❌ Implementation Cost = 1 (Very high cost)

### Long-Term Retention Risk
- ❌ Long-Term Retention Risk = 1 (Very high risk)

### Monetization Depth
- ❌ Monetization Depth = 1 (Very shallow)

### Expected Value
- ❌ Expected Value < $5k

### Risk Score
- ❌ Risk Score > 20 (Very High Risk)

### Opportunity Cost
- ❌ Opportunity Cost > Current Product EV × 2

